{
  "text": "and lim Notice that the first expression coincides exactly with the pure \u03c7PT calculation, Eq.(74). Similarly for W LLRR , the O(p 2 ) coefficient \u22123/8 and O(p 4 ) l 9 coefficient +3/2 coincide with the corresponding coefficients of Eq.(75). Both coefficients are \u221216 times the corresponding coefficient for W LRLR . However, it turns out that the O(p 4 ) l 3 coefficient for W LRLR which is also \u221216 times the corresponding coefficient in W LRLR differs by a factor 5 from the one previously obtained in \u03c7PT, Eq.(75), so that the total slope Q 2 coefficient differs by approximately a factor \u223c 2. The origin of this discrepancy is not well understood by us. We have performed a variety of consistency checks on the 5D calculation and we do not see any possibility of deviations which would alter the fact that W LLRR and W LRLR differ by this factor \u221216. It seems possible to us that the problem might lie with the sole and rather subtle \u03c7PT calculation of the l 3 dependence of W LLRR . [CITATION_1] ",
